## 1. Competition Intel Summary

### Goal
Segment the **recto surface** (papyrus sheet facing the scroll center) within 3D CT scans of carbonized Herculaneum scrolls.

### Evaluation Metric

```
Score = 0.30 × TopoScore + 0.35 × SurfaceDice@τ(2.0) + 0.35 × VOI_score
```

| Metric | Weight | What It Rewards | What It Penalizes |
|--------|--------|-----------------|-------------------|
| **SurfaceDice** | 35% | Geometric accuracy within 2.0 tolerance | Misaligned surfaces |
| **VOI Score** | 35% | Instance consistency | Splits & mergers |
| **TopoScore** | 30% | Topological correctness | Holes, handles, sheet-switches |

> [!CAUTION]
> Even a few **holes** in your mask can tank the TopoScore. Topology > voxel accuracy.

